# PERF-7 — Stress-test runtime artifacts. The synthetic 500-page
# fixture is generated at test time (see
# Packages/RedactionEngine/Tests/.../StressTests/StressFixtureBuilder.swift)
# and the result JSON is rewritten on each baseline run. The
# committed `stress-baseline.json` is intentionally NOT ignored.
stress-corpus-*.pdf
StressFixtures/
Packages/RedactionEngine/Tests/RedactionEngineTests/IntegrationTests/StressTests/stress-result.json

# Claude Code agent scratch — per-machine session state, not source.
# (`.claude/commands/` and `.claude/reports/` ARE tracked.)
.claude/prompts/
.claude/worktrees/

# SEC-6 — The detached Ed25519 signature + public key are PUBLIC artifacts
# (the private signing key in ~/.resecta-data/ never enters the repo). They
# are COMMITTED so a clean clone / Release archive ships a verifiable
# gazetteer manifest; absence would degrade Auto-Detect to non-gazetteer
# detectors with the SEC-7 banner (REL-1 / D11-config-golive-F2).
# The pair is produced by the DataPipeline signing step (gmake install-assets /
# scripts/reinstall_signatures.sh) and asserted by
# SignedManifestTests.committedSignaturePairVerifiesShippedManifest; the
# committed bytes are the currently-signed pair.
# (no ignore lines — both files are tracked; Jesse commits the binaries per CLAUDE.md 2.8)

# UITestFixtures has no ignore lines — both fixtures are committed
# synthetics: test_sample.pdf (611-byte single-pager from RawPDFBuilder
# primitives, F03/CAT-254) and uitest_multipage.pdf (23-page workpaper,
# regenerable via Scripts/generate_uitest_multipage.py, q38 — it replaced
# a formerly gitignored real-document copy that served the
# `--multipageDoc` launch hook), so clean checkouts run the multipage UI
# tests without manual fixture restoration.
